No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob tsi ebɛŋkɛ etsɛ Isak, ni Isak tara ehe, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Gbee lɛ Yakob gbee ni, shi niji lɛ Esau niji ni.”
Isak yooo Yakob, ejaakɛ eniji ahe yɛ tsɔi sulaŋŋ tamɔ enyɛmi Esau niji ahe pɛpɛɛpɛ. Kɛkɛ ni Isak jɔɔ lɛ.
Kɛkɛ ni ebi akɛ, “Ani bo mibi Esau pɔtɛɛ nɛ lo?” Ni Yakob kɛɛ akɛ, “Mi ni”.
Kɛkɛ ni Isak kɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Okɛ niyenii lɛ abahã mi koni maye mibi milɛloo lɛ eko koni majɔɔ bo.” No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob kɛ niyenii lɛ bahã lɛ, ni eye. Ebahã Isak wain hu, ni enu.
Kɛkɛ ni etsɛ Isak kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Mibi, tsi obɛŋkɛ mi koo koni obashwɔ minaa!”
Ni etsi ebɛŋkɛ ni ebashwɔ enaa, ni Isak nu Yakob atadei lɛ amli ŋma lɛ, ni ejɔɔ lɛ ekɛɛ akɛ, “Kwɛ bɔ ni mibi lɛ he jeɔ ŋma, tamɔ ŋa frɔ̃frɔ̃ ni Yehowa ejɔɔ.
Nyɔŋmɔ ahã bo ŋwɛi bɔ kɛ shikpɔŋ mli fɔ lɛ eko, kɛ ŋmãa kɛ wain babaoo hu.

Maji asɔ̃mɔ bo, ni je lɛŋ maji akoto bo. Ye onyɛmimɛi lɛ anɔ lumɔ, ni onyɛ bihii lɛ akoto bo. Mɔ fɛɛ mɔ ni aaalomɔ bo lɛ, alomɔ lɛ, ni mɔ fɛɛ mɔ ni aaajɔɔ bo lɛ, ajɔɔ lɛ!” Esau kpa fai koni Isak ajɔɔ lɛ

Be ni Isak egbe Yakob jɔɔmɔ lɛ naa ni Yakob kɛɛ ejeɔ etsɛ Isak hiɛ nɔŋŋ pɛ lɛ, naa enyɛmi Esau hu; ejɛ emilɛ lɛ eba. 31Ni lɛ hu efee niyenii kɛ ŋɔɔmɔ ni ekɛmiiba ebahã etsɛ. Ni ekɛɛ etsɛ akɛ, “Ataa, tee shi ni ota shi ni oye obi milɛloo lɛ eko koni ojɔɔ mi.”
Etsɛ Isak bi lɛ akɛ, “Bo namɔ ni?” Ni Esau to he akɛ, “Mi, okromɔbi Esau ni.”
Kɛkɛ ni Isak he kpokpo blibli waa diɛŋtsɛ, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Namɔ mɔ ji mɔ ni kɛ milɛloo bahã mi ni miye fɛɛ dani obaa nɛɛ, ni mijɔɔ lɛ, ni aaajɔɔ lɛ hu lɛ?”
Be ni Esau nu etsɛ wiemɔi lɛ, ebo waa diɛŋtsɛ kɛ awerɛhoo babaoo ni ekɛɛ etsɛ Isak akɛ, “Mi hu jɔɔmɔ mi eko, Ataa!”
Shi Isak kɛɛ, “Onyɛmi lɛ kɛ shishiumɔ ebahe ojɔɔmɔ lɛ kɛtee.”
Esau kɛɛ, “Egbɛi Yakob ni awo lɛ lɛ, ebala lɛ. Shii enyɔ sɔŋŋ ni eshishiu mi nɛ; mikromɔbi gbɛnaa lɛ eshɔ̃, ni agbɛnɛ ebahe mijɔɔmɔ lɛ hu!” Ni Esau bi etsɛ akɛ, “Ani oshwɛɛɛ jɔɔmɔ lɛ eko ohãaa mi?”
Isak to he ekɛɛ Esau akɛ; “Mifee lɛ onuŋtsɔ, ni mikɛ enyɛmimɛi lɛ fɛɛ efee etsuji. Miŋɔ ŋmãa kɛ wain mihã lɛ; ni bo lɛ, mɛni mafee mahã bo mɔ, mibi?”
Kɛkɛ ni Esau kɛɛ etsɛ akɛ, “Ataa, ani jɔɔmɔ kome pɛ kɛkɛ oyɔɔ? Hã mi jɔɔmɔ ko kɛ̃, Ataa!” Ni Esau jwa yaafo.
Etsɛ Isak here nɔ, ni ekɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Shikpɔŋ ni fɔ bɛ mli nɔ ooohi, kɛ he ni ŋwɛi bɔ enyɔɔɔ yɛ.
Oklante naa oyi aaana wala yɛ, ni onyɛmi lɛ ooosɔ̃mɔ. Shi aaaba mli akɛ, kɛ opele ohe lɛ,oookpɔ̃ ohe yɛ edɛŋ.”
Esau nyɛ Yakob yɛ jɔɔmɔ ni etsɛ jɔɔ lɛ lɛ hewɔ. Ekɛɛ yɛ eyitsoŋ akɛ, “Etsɛŋ tsɔ ko ni aaafee mitsɛ yara, kɛkɛ lɛ magbe minyɛmi Yakob.”
Shi abagba Rebeka ebi nukpa Esau wiemɔi nɛɛ, ni etsu ayatsɛ Yakob, ebi gbekɛ lɛ, kɛba ni ekɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Naa, onyɛmi Esau kɛ gbe ni ebaagbe bo miihã ehe tsui.
No hewɔ lɛ, mibi, bo mi toi, joo foi oya kɛya minyɛmi Laban ŋɔɔ yɛ Haran
ni okɛ lɛ ayahi shi gbii fioo ko kɛyashi beyinɔ ni onyɛmi lɛ tsui he aaajɔ;
kɛyashi beyinɔ ni onyɛmi lɛ mlifu lɛ naa aaaba shi ni ehiɛ aaakpa nɔ ni ofee lɛ lɛ nɔ; kɛkɛ lɛ matsu ni abaŋɔ bo kɛku sɛɛ kɛba. Mɛɛba nyɛyi enyɔ lɛ fɛɛ nyɛaaŋmɛɛ mi gbi kome?”
Kɛkɛ ni Rebeka kɛɛ Isak akɛ, “Esau ŋamɛi Hityei lɛ ehã mijeŋshihilɛ eje mitsine. Kɛji Yakob hu aaaŋɔ shikpɔŋ nɛɛ nɔ Hityei nɛɛ eko akɛ eŋa tamɔ mɛnɛɛmɛi lɛ, no lɛ faŋ nɔ ni migbo moŋ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Isak tsɛ Yakob ni ejɔɔ lɛ, ni ewo lɛ akpɔ ni ekɛɛ, “Kaaŋɔ yoo yɛ Kanaan yei lɛ ateŋ.
Yaa onyɛ tsɛ Betuel we lɛ, yɛ Mesopotamia, ni oyaŋɔ onyɛ nyɛmi nuu Laban biyei lɛ eko akɛ oŋa.
Nyɔŋmɔ Ofe lɛ ajɔɔ bo, ni ehã oshwere ni owo shwiei babaoo koni oshwiei atsɔ̃ majimaji asafo.
Bɔ ni ejɔɔ Abraham lɛ, ejɔɔ bo kɛ oshwiei nakai nɔŋŋ koni ogbɔtoo shikpɔŋ nɛɛ ni Nyɔŋmɔ kɛhã otsɛ Abraham lɛ atsɔ̃ onɔ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Isak wo Yakob gbɛ koni eya Mesopotamia yɛ Aramnyo Betuel bi Laban ni ji Yakob kɛ Esau nyɛ Rebeka nyɛmi nuu lɛ ŋɔɔ.
Esau na akɛ Isak ejɔɔ Yakob, ni ewo lɛ gbɛ kɛtee Mesopotamia koni eyaŋɔ yoo yɛ jɛi.
Ena ele hu akɛ be ni Isak jɔɔ Yakob lɛ, ewo lɛ akpɔ akɛ ekaŋɔ yoo yɛ Kanaan yei lɛ ateŋ, ni Yakob ebo etsɛ kɛ enyɛ toi ni etee Mesopotamia.
Esau na hu akɛ etsɛ nyãaa Kanaan yei lɛ ahe.
Enɛɛmɛi ahewɔ lɛ, Esau yiŋ etee Abraham bi Ishmael ŋɔɔ, ni eyaŋɔ ebiyoo Mahalat, Nabaiot nyɛmi yoo lɛ, efata eŋãmɛi ni eyɔɔ lɛ ahe.
Yakob jɛ Beersheba ni eyiŋ eeya Haran.
Eshɛ he ko ni eto jɛi ejaakɛ hulu enyɔ shi. Ekɔ jɛi tɛi lɛ eko etsɔle, ni ekã jɛi ewɔ.
Ni ela ni aŋtswere ko ma shikpɔŋ ni eyiteŋ eyashi ŋwɛi. Nyɔŋmɔ bɔfoi miikwɔ miikpeleke shi,
ni Yehowa damɔ aŋtswere lɛ yiteŋ ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Mi ji Yehowa, otsɛ Abraham Nyɔŋmɔ, kɛ Isak Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ; shikpɔŋ ni okã nɔ nɛɛ, bo kɛ oshwiei mikɛbaahã.
Oshwiei aaafa tamɔ shikpɔŋ mlu, ni ooogbɛ oshwã anai kɛ bokã kɛ kooyi kɛ wuoyi. Bo kɛ oshwiei amli aaajɛ ajɔɔ shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ akutsei fɛɛ.
Na ole akɛ mikɛ bo yɛ ni he fɛɛ he ni oyaa lɛ, mabu ohe, ni mikɛ bo aaaba shikpɔŋ nɛɛ nɔ ekoŋŋ, ejaakɛ mishiŋ bo kɛyaashi beyinɔ ni mafee nɔ ni mitsi tã mikɛɛ bo lɛ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob hiɛ tsɛ̃ kɛjɛ ewɔ lɛ mli, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Yehowa yɛ biɛ kwa, ni mi lɛ mileee nɛɛ!”
Yakob she gbeyei, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Biɛ nɛɛ yɛ gbeyei eei! Biɛ nɛɛ jeee he ko he ko akɛ Nyɔŋmɔ we, ni ŋwɛi naa agbo nɛ!”
Yakob te shi leebi maŋkpa ni etee tɛ lɛ ni etsɔle lɛ shi ema shi ekɛto okadi, ni efɔse mu eshwie nɔ.
Ewo jɛi Betel; shi sa lɛ, nakai maŋ lɛ gbɛi ji Luz.
Yakob wo shi ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Kɛji Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ mi aaahi shi, ni eeebu mihe yɛ gbɛ ni miyanyiɛ nɛɛ mli, ni eeehã miŋmãa maye kɛ atade mawo,
ni maku misɛɛ maba mitsɛ we lɛ kɛ omanye lɛ, no lɛ Yehowa aaatsɔ̃ miNyɔŋmɔ,
ni nɛkɛ tɛ nɛɛ ni mikɛma shi mikɛto okadi nɛɛ aaatsɔ̃ Nyɔŋmɔ we; ni maŋɔ nibii fɛɛ ni ooohã mi lɛ amlijaa nyɔŋma kome mahã bo.”
Yakob wo enane nɔ yɛ egbɛfaa lɛ mli, ni eyashɛ bokãgbɛbii ashikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ.
Be ni ewo ehiɛ nɔ lɛ, ena nubu ko yɛ ŋa lɛ nɔ, ni ena too kui etɛ̃ bumɔ shi yɛ he ejaakɛ nakai bu lɛ mli nu ahãa amɛ amɛnuɔ. Tɛ ni kã bu lɛ naa lɛ da.
Kɛji too kui lɛ fɛɛ ebabua amɛhe naa yɛ bu lɛ he lɛ, tookwɛlɔi lɛ kokloɔ tɛ lɛ kɛjeɔ bu lɛ naa ni amɛhãa toi lɛ nu, kɛkɛ lɛ amɛkoklo tɛ lɛ amɛto bu lɛ naa ekoŋŋ yɛ egbɛhe.
Yakob bi tookwɛlɔi lɛ akɛ, “Minyɛmimɛi, nɛgbɛ nyɛjɛ?” Amɛto he akɛ, “Wɔjɛ Haran.”
Yakob bi amɛ akɛ, “Ani nyɛle Nahor bi Laban lɛ lo?” Amɛto he akɛ, “Wɔle lɛ.”
Esaa ebi amɛ akɛ, “Eyɛ jogbaŋŋ lo?”
Yakob kɛɛ akɛ, “Naa, je nako kwraa. Eshɛko be ni abuaa toi lɛ anaa. Nyɛhãa amɛ nu amɛnua koni nyɛhãa amɛyayea nii.”
Shi amɛto he akɛ, “Wɔnyɛŋ amɛ nu wɔhã akɛ ja abua too kuikui lɛ fɛɛ naa kɛkpe, ni akoklo tɛ lɛ kɛje bu lɛ naa dani wɔɔnyɛ amɛ nu wɔhã.”
Be ni Yakob kɛ amɛ wieɔ lolo lɛ, Rahel kɛ etsɛ toi lɛ bashɛ jɛi; ejaakɛ lɛ ekwɛɔ amɛ.
Be ni Yakob na Rahel, enyɛ nyɛmi nuu Laban biyoo lɛ, kɛ enyɛ nyɛmi nuu Laban toi lɛ, Yakob tsi etee ni eyakoklo tɛ lɛ kɛje bu lɛ naa, ni ehã enyɛ nyɛmi nuu Laban toi lɛ nu amɛnu.
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob shwɔ Rahel naa, ni Yakob jwa yaafo.
Yakob kɛɛ Rahel akɛ, “Otsɛ wekunyo ji mi, ni Rebeka binuu ji mi.”
Be ni Laban nu enyɛmi yoo bi Yakob he sane lɛ, esha foi etee lɛ kpeemɔ. Eloo Yakob atuu, ni eshwɔ enaa. Ekɛ lɛ ba ewe lɛ. Yakob gba Laban saji fɛɛ ni ba lɛ,
ni Laban kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Asonɔkwa, mi diɛŋtsɛ mila ji bo!” Yakob kɛ lɛ hi shi nyɔŋ kome.

Ni Laban kɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Akɛni miwekuyo ji bo hewɔ lɛ ani esa akɛ osɔ̃mɔ mi yaka lo? Tsɔ̃ɔmɔ bɔ ni obaahe mi.” 16Laban yɛ biyei enyɔ. Onukpa lɛ gbɛi ji Lea, ni gbekɛ lɛ gbɛi ji Rahel. 17Lea hiŋmɛii yɛ sukusuku, shi Rahel hiɛ yɛ fɛo ni egbɔmɔtso hu yɛ fɛo.
Yakob sumɔ Rahel, no hewɔ lɛ, ekɛɛ Laban akɛ, “Mibasɔ̃mɔ bo afii kpawo yɛ Rahel, obiyoo fioo lɛ hewɔ.”
Laban to he akɛ, “Ehi akɛ mikɛ lɛ ahã bo fe nɔ ni mikɛ lɛ aaahã nuu kroko. Okɛ mi ahi shi.”
No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob sɔ̃mɔ afii kpawo yɛ Rahel hewɔ; ni suɔmɔ sɔŋŋ ni esumɔɔ Rahel hewɔ lɛ, afii lɛ ho oya yɛ ehiɛ tamɔ gbii fioo ko kɛkɛ.
Agbɛnɛ Yakob kɛɛ Laban akɛ, “Okɛ miŋa lɛ ahã mi koni mikɛ lɛ ahi shi ejaakɛ migbe misɔ̃ɔmɔ be lɛ naa. 22Kɛkɛ ni Laban bua jɛi bii lɛ fɛɛ anaa, ni eŋmɛ okplɔ̃.
Shi be ni shɛ gbɛkɛ lɛ, ekɛ ebiyoo Lea moŋ yahã Yakob ni Yakob kɛ Lea wɔ. 24 (Laban kɛ eweyoo ko ni gbɛi ji Zilpa lɛ hã ebiyoo Lea akɛ Lea weyoo).
Be ni je tsɛre lɛ, Yakob na akɛ Lea ni. Kɛkɛ ni Yakob kɛɛ Laban akɛ, ‘Mɛni sane oye mi nɛɛ? Ani jeee Rahel hewɔ misɔ̃mɔ bo lɛ? Mɛɛ hewɔ mɔ ni oshishiu mi nɛkɛ?’ ”
Laban to he akɛ, “Wɔshikpɔŋ nɛɛ nɔ lɛ, afeee nakai. Ahãaa gbekɛ gbãlã dani ahã onukpa gbãlã.
Gbee mɔ nɛ otsi lɛ naa ni wɔkɛ mɔ kome lɛ hu baahã bo, kɛji osɔ̃mɔ mi afii kpawo kroko.”
Yakob fee nakai; egbe Lea otsi lɛ naa. Kɛkɛ ni Laban kɛ ebiyoo Rahel hu hã lɛ gbãlã.
(Laban kɛ eweyoo Bilha hã ebiyoo Rahel akɛ Rahel weyoo).
Rahel hu bawɔ Yakob ŋɔɔ. Yakob sumɔ Rahel fe Lea; ni esɔ̃mɔ Laban afii kpawo kroko yɛ Rahel hewɔ.
Be ni Yehowa na akɛ Yakob sumɔɔɔ Lea lɛ, egbele Lea musu naa, shi eŋa Rahel musu naa ni efee kene.
Lea na musu ni efɔ binuu. Ewo lɛ Ruben, ni ekɛɛ, “Ejaakɛ Yehowa ena mimanehulu lɛ. Agbɛnɛ lɛ miwu baasumɔ mi.”
Lea na musu ekoŋŋ, ni efɔ binuu. Ekɛɛ akɛ, “Akɛni Yehowa enu akɛ asumɔɔɔ mi hewɔ lɛ, ehã mi binuu nɛɛ hu.” Ni ewo lɛ Simeon.
Esaa ena musu, ni efɔ binuu ekoŋŋ. Ekɛɛ akɛ, “Enɛ lɛ, agbɛnɛ, miwu kɛ ehe baakpɛtɛ mihe, ejaakɛ mikɛ lɛ efɔ bihii etɛ̃.” Enɛ hewɔ lɛ, ewo gbekɛ lɛ Levi.
Be ni Rahel na akɛ ekɛ Yakob fɔɔɔ lɛ, ebɔi enyɛmi yoo Lea lɛ he awuŋayeli, ni ekɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Okɛ mi afɔ, kɛjeee nakai lɛ magbo!”
Yakob mli wo Rahel la, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Ani mi ji Nyɔŋmɔ ni etsi omusuŋbii anaa lɛ?”
Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛɛ, “Mikɛ miweyoo Bilha miihã bo ŋɔɔ lɛ ni okɛ lɛ afɔ ashwie mishuɔ nɔ mɔ, koni mi hu mana bii kɛtsɔ̃ enɔ.”
No hewɔ lɛ, Rahel kɛ eweyoo Bilha hã Yakob gbãlã. Bilha yawɔ Yakob ŋɔɔ;
Bilha na musu, ni ekɛ Yakob fɔ binuu.
Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛɛ, “Nyɔŋmɔ eye misane lɛ ehã mi, ebo mi toi, ni ehã mi binuu.” No hewɔ lɛ, ewo abifao lɛ Dan.
Bilha, Rahel weyoo lɛ, na musu ekoŋŋ, ni ekɛ Yakob fɔ binuu ni ji enyɔ.
Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛɛ akɛ, “Mikɛ minyɛmi yoo lɛ enɔ nɔmɔ ni mli wa, ni miye kunim.” No hewɔ lɛ, ewo abifao lɛ Naftali.
Be ni Lea na akɛ ekpa fɔmɔ lɛ, ekɛ eweyoo Zilpa hã Yakob gbãlã.
Lea weyoo Zilpa lɛ kɛ Yakob fɔ binuu.
Lea kɛɛ akɛ, “Omanye sane nɛ;” no hewɔ lɛ, ewo abifao lɛ Gad.
Lea weyoo Zilpa kɛ Yakob fɔ binuu ni ji enyɔ;
ni Lea kɛɛ akɛ, “Mina miishɛɛ ejaakɛ yei aaatsɛ mi yoo ni yɔɔ miishɛɛ;” ni ewo abifao lɛ Asher.
Be ni ŋmãakuu be shɛ lɛ, Ruben yana suɔmɔ tso yibii ko yɛ ŋa lɛ nɔ, ni etse eko, ni ekɛbahã enyɛ Lea. Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛɛ Lea akɛ, “Miikpa bo fai ni ohã mi obi lɛ suɔmɔ tso yibii lɛ eko.”

Shi Lea kɛɛ Rahel akɛ, “Aso ni oshɔ̃ miwu lɛ, no faaa hãaa bo, obaashɔ̃ mibi lɛ suɔmɔ tso yibii lɛ hu?” Rahel to he akɛ, “Kɛji ooohã mi obi lɛ suɔmɔ tso yibii lɛ eko lɛ, no lɛ obaanyɛ oyawɔ Yakob ŋɔɔ ŋmɛnɛ.”

No hewɔ lɛ, gbɛkɛ mli be ni Yakob jɛ ŋmɔ mli ebaa lɛ, Lea je kpo ni ekɛ lɛ yakpe, ni ekɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Ŋmɛnɛ, ja obawɔ miŋɔɔ ejaakɛ mikɛ mibi lɛ suɔmɔ tso yibii lɛ ebɔ bo apaa!” No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob kɛ lɛ wɔ nakai nyɔɔŋ lɛ mli.
Nyɔŋmɔ bo Lea sɔlemɔ toi, ena musu; ni ekɛ Yakob fɔ binuu ni ji enumɔ. 18Kɛkɛ ni Lea kɛɛ akɛ, “Nyɔŋmɔ ehã mi mipaabɔɔnii, ejaakɛ mikɛ miweyoo lɛ ehã miwu gbãlã;” ni ewo abifao lɛ Isakar.
Ni Lea na musu ekoŋŋ, ni ekɛ Yakob fɔ binuu ni ji ekpaa.
Kɛkɛ ni Lea kɛɛ akɛ, “Nyɔŋmɔ ehã mi gbãlãnii fɛɛfɛo. Agbɛnɛ miwu baawo mihiɛ nyam, ejaakɛ mikɛ lɛ efɔ bihii ekpaa sɔŋŋ.” No hewɔ lɛ, ewo gbekɛ lɛ Zebulon.
Enɛ sɛɛ lɛ Lea fɔ biyoo, ni ewo lɛ Dina.
Kɛkɛ ni Nyɔŋmɔ kai Rahel; Nyɔŋmɔ bo esɔlemɔ toi, ni egbele emusu naa.
Rahel na musu, ni efɔ binuu, ni ekɛɛ akɛ, “Nyɔŋmɔ ejie mihiɛgbele lɛ.”
Ewo gbekɛ lɛ Yosef, eshishi ji, “Yehowa ahã mafɔ binuu ekoŋŋ.”
Okɛ miŋamɛi kɛ nibii ni misɔ̃mɔ bo yɛ amɛhewɔ lɛ ahã mi ni maya ejaakɛ bo diɛŋtsɛ ole bɔ ni misɔ̃mɔ bo mihã.”
Shi Laban kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Kɛ oooŋmɛ mi gbɛ ni mawie lɛ, mitsɔ̃ gbalɛ nɔ mina mile akɛ bo ohewɔ ni Yehowa ejɔɔ mi nɛɛ.
Tsɔ̃ɔmɔ mi bɔ ni obaahe mi, ni mahã bo.”
Yakob kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Bo diɛŋtsɛ ole bɔ ni misɔ̃mɔ bo mihã kɛ bɔ hu ni okooloi lɛ eshwere yɛ midɛŋ.
Ejaakɛ be ni miba lɛ, kooloi fioo ko kɛkɛ oyɔɔ; shi amrɔ nɛɛ amɛshwere babaoo; mi mihewɔ Yehowa ejɔɔ bo babaoo nɛɛ. Shi agbɛnɛ mɛɛbe mabua nɔ ko naa mahã mi diɛŋtsɛ miwe hu.”
Laban bi lɛ akɛ, “Mɛni mahã bo?” Yakob hã lɛ hetoo akɛ, “Kaahã mi nɔ ko nɔ ko. Kɛ ooofee nɔ ni mibatsɔ̃ɔ bo nɛɛ ohã mi lɛ, no lɛ masaa malɛ okooloi lɛ ni makwɛ amɛ ekoŋŋ.

Ŋmɛnɛ hã ni makpa otoi lɛ fɛɛ mli ni mahala toobi fɛɛ toobi ni he yɔɔ truntrãi kɛ damdam yɛ gwantɛŋi lɛ amli, kɛ nii ni he yɔɔ damdam kɛ nii ni he yɔɔ truntrãi yɛ abotiai lɛ ateŋ lɛ. Nomɛi aaatsɔ minyɔmɔwoo.

Ni kɛfee sɛɛ ni ooobakwɛ minyɔmɔwoo lɛ, miye bo anɔkwale jio, miyeko bo anɔkwale jio, obaana. Abotiai lɛ amli eko fɛɛ eko ni he bɛ truntrãi kɛ damdam kɛ gwantɛŋi lɛ amli nii ni he diii lɛ kɛ ooona eko yɛ midɛŋ lɛ, belɛ no lɛ juunii ni.”
Laban to he akɛ, “Ojogbaŋŋ; afee bɔ ni okɛɛ nɛɛ.”

Ni nakai gbi lɛ Laban jie too kpakpoi ni he yɔɔ truntrãi kɛ damdam lɛ kɛ abotia yei ni he yɔɔ truntrãi kɛ damdam lɛ, eko fɛɛ eko ni eyɛŋ ta ehe, kɛ gwantɛŋbi fɛɛ gwantɛŋbi ni diɔ, ni etu amɛ ewo ebii lɛ adɛŋ.
Kɛkɛ ni ekɛ ebii lɛ shi Yakob kɛtee he kroko ni jɛkɛmɔ ji gbii etɛ̃ gbɛnyiɛmɔ, ni Yakob kwɛ Laban toi ni shwɛ lɛ.
Agbɛnɛ Yakob kɔlɔ libne tsei ŋmɔji kɛ luz tsei kɛ blɔfoŋkatiɛ tsei ni eye amɛhe sãmãi yɛji, ni ehã tsei lɛ amli eyɛji lɛ je shi.
Ekɛ tsei ni eye amɛhe sãmãi nɛɛ shwie tsesei ni toi lɛ banuɔ nu yɛ mli lɛ amli, bɔ ni toi lɛ aaana sãmãi lɛ kɛji amɛba nu lɛ numɔ lɛ; ejaakɛ kɛ amɛba nu lɛ numɔ lɛ, toohii lɛ kwɔɔ tooyei lɛ yɛ jɛi.
No hewɔ lɛ, kɛ toohii lɛ kwɔ too yei lɛ yɛ tsei lɛ ahiɛ lɛ, toi lɛ fɔfɔɔ toobii ni he yɔɔ sãmãisãmãi kɛ nii ni he yɔɔ truntrãi kɛ damdam.
Yakob tserɛ too gwantɛŋbii lɛ eto afã, ni etsɔ̃mɔ toi lɛ ahiɛ ehã Laban toi ni he yɔɔ sãmãisãmãi lɛ kɛ nii ni diɔ lɛ fɛɛ. Ekɛ lɛ diɛŋtsɛ etoo ku lɛ to afã, ni ekɛ amɛ futuuu Laban toi lɛ.
Kɛ toi ni yɔɔ hewalɛ lɛ kɛ amɛhe miina bɔlɛ lɛ, Yakob kɛ tsei lɛ shwieɔ tsesei lɛ ahiɛ, koni toi lɛ ana bɔlɛ yɛ tsei lɛ ateŋ.
Shi toi ni yɔɔ wudɔwudɔ lɛ ekɛ tsei lɛ eshwieee amɛhiɛ. No hewɔ lɛ, toi wudɔwudɔi lɛ tsɔmɔ Laban nii, ni nii ni yɔɔ hewalɛ lɛ tsɔmɔ Yakob nii.
Enɛ hã Yakob shwere waa naakpa. Ena toi babaoo kɛ weyei kɛ wehii kɛ yoomai kɛ tejii.
Yakob nu ni Laban bihii lɛ miiwiewie akɛ, “Yakob eshɔ̃ wɔtsɛ nii fɛɛ; wɔtsɛ nii lɛ ekɛna ehe nɛɛ.”
Agbɛnɛ Yakob na akɛ gbii etɛ̃ nɛɛ Laban tseee ehiɛ ehãaa lɛ dɔŋŋ tamɔ sa lɛ.
Kɛkɛ ni Yehowa kɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Kuu osɛɛ kɛya otsɛmɛi kɛ owekumɛi ashikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ, ni mi kɛ bo aaahi shi.”
No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob tsu ayatsɛ Rahel kɛ Lea kɛba ŋa lɛ nɔ, he ni etoi lɛ yɔɔ lɛ,
ni ekɛɛ amɛ akɛ, “Mina akɛ gbii etɛ̃ nɛɛ nyɛtsɛ tseee ehiɛ ehãaa mi dɔŋŋ tamɔ sa lɛ. Shi Nyɔŋmɔ ni mitsɛ jaa lɛ kɛ mi yɛ.
Nyɛ diɛŋtsɛ nyɛle akɛ mihewalɛ fɛɛ mikɛsɔ̃mɔ nyɛtsɛ;
kɛ̃lɛ nyɛtsɛ shishiu mi, ni etsake minyɔmɔwo shii nyɔŋma; shi Nyɔŋmɔ hãaa lɛ hegbɛ ni efee mi efɔŋ ko.
Kɛji ekɛɛ akɛ, ‘Toi kɛ amɛhe truntrãi lɛ aaatsɔ onɔ lɛ, kɛkɛ lɛ toi lɛ fɛɛ efɔ bii kɛ amɛhe damdam.’
Nɛkɛ Nyɔŋmɔ fee ni eshɔ̃ nyɛtsɛ kooloi lɛ ehã mi.
“Toi lɛ amusunamɔ be mli lɛ, miwo mihiɛ nɔ, ni mina yɛ lamɔ mli akɛ too kpakpoi ni kwɔɔ tooyei lɛ, amɛhe yɛ truntrãi kɛ damdam kɛ ŋwãtãŋwãtã.
Kɛkɛ ni Nyɔŋmɔ bɔfo lɛ kɛɛ mi yɛ lamɔ lɛ mli akɛ, ‘Yakob!’ Ni mikɛɛ akɛ, ‘Naa mi!’
Ni ekɛɛ mi akɛ, ‘Wo ohiɛ nɔ, ni ooona akɛ too kpakpoi lɛ fɛɛ ni kwɔɔ tooyei lɛ amɛhe truntrãi kɛ damdam kɛ ŋwãtãŋwãtã ejaakɛ mina nii fɛɛ ni Laban feɔ bo lɛ.

Mi ji Nyɔŋmɔ mɔ ni jie ehe kpo etsɔ̃ɔ bo yɛ Betel, he ni oŋɔ tɛ okɛto okadi yɛ, ni ofɔ okadi tɛ lɛ mu, ni owo mi shi yɛ lɛ. Agbɛnɛ tee shi oyá ni oya; jee shikpɔŋ nɛɛ nɔ koni oku osɛɛ oya shikpɔŋ nɔ he ni afɔ bo yɛ lɛ.’ ”
Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛ Lea here nɔ, ni amɛkɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Wɔbɛ gbɛfaŋ nɔ ko loo gboshinii ko dɔŋŋ yɛ wɔtsɛ we lɛ.
Ani jeee mɛi kpɔji ebuɔ wɔ? Ejaakɛ ehɔ̃ɔ wɔ, ni eye wɔyi nii lɛ hu.
Shi nii fɛɛ ni Nyɔŋmɔ eshɔ̃ yɛ wɔtsɛ dɛ lɛ, no ji wɔ kɛ wɔbii anɔ. No hewɔ lɛ, nɔ fɛɛ nɔ ni Nyɔŋmɔ ekɛɛ bo lɛ feemɔ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob te shi, ni eŋɔ ebii kɛ eŋãmɛi lɛ etara yoomai anɔ;
ni ekpala kooloi lɛ kɛ enii fɛɛ ni ena lɛ, ni ji nii ni ena yɛ Mesopotamia lɛ, ni eŋɔ eshwie nɔ kɛmiiya etsɛ Isak ŋɔɔ yɛ Kanaan shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ.
Laban etee eyaaku etoi lɛ ahe tsɔi, ni Rahel ju etsɛ shĩa amãgãi lɛ.
Yakob laka Laban, Aramnyo lɛ ejaakɛ ekɛ efoijee lɛ tee Laban.
Yakob jo foi kɛ nɔ fɛɛ nɔ ni eyɔɔ, ni etee eyafo Eufrate Faa lɛ, ni ewo eyi ema he ni Gilead gɔji lɛ yɔɔ lɛ gbɛ.
No hewɔ lɛ, Laban ŋɔ ewekumɛi efata ehe, ni etiu Yakob gbii kpawo gbɛ kɛyashi eyanina lɛ yɛ Gilead gɔji lɛ anɔ.
Shi Nyɔŋmɔ jie ehe kpo etsɔ̃ɔ Laban, Aramnyo lɛ, yɛ wɔ mli ni ekɛɛ Laban akɛ, “Kwɛmɔ ni ahi koni okɛ Yakob akawie wiemɔ fɔŋ ko.”
Laban yanina Yakob. Nɛkɛ be mli lɛ, Yakob eshi ebuu yɛ gɔji lɛ anɔ; ni Laban kɛ ewebii lɛ hu shi amɛbuu yɛ Gilead gɔji lɛ anɔ.
Laban kɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Mɛni ofee nɛɛ? Olaka mi ni oŋɔ mibiyei lɛ kɛmiiya tamɔ mɛi ni aŋɔ amɛ nom yɛ ta mli nɛɛ?
Mɛɛ hewɔ ni ojo foi dujiaŋ ni oshɛɛɛ mi koni kulɛ mikɛ lala kɛ milɛ̃ kɛ kpãa saŋku ayajie bo gbɛ kɛ miishɛɛ?
Ni mɛɛ hewɔ ohãaa mana hegbɛ koni mashwɔ minabihii kɛ mibiyei lɛ anaa mikɛ amɛ aye shɛɛ lɛ? Nɔ ni ofee lɛ kwashiai asane oye nɛɛ.
Kulɛ manyɛ mafee bo efɔŋ; shi otsɛ Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ kɛ mi wie nyɔɔŋ nɛɛ mli, ni ekɛɛ mi akɛ, ‘Kwɛmɔ ohe ni ahi koni okɛ Yakob akawie wiemɔ fɔŋ ko.’
Agbɛnɛ, yaa oyaa nɛɛ, ejaakɛ ohiɛ etsɔ̃ otsɛ we lɛ; shi mɛɛba mɔ ni oju mimãgãi lɛ?”
Yakob to he, ni ekɛɛ, “Miyashe gbeyei akɛ ekolɛ oooshɔ̃ obiyei lɛ yɛ midɛŋ akrananaa.
Shi mɔ fɛɛ mɔ dɛŋ ni ooona owɔŋ lɛ yɛ lɛ agbe lɛ. Taomɔ nɔ ni ji onɔ yɛ minibii nɛɛ ateŋ, yɛ wekumɛi ni yɔɔ biɛ nɛɛ ahiɛ koni okɔ onii.” Shi Yakob leee akɛ Rahel ni eju amãgãi lɛ.
Kɛkɛ ni Laban bote Yakob buu lɛ mli kɛ Lea buu lɛ mli kɛ weyei enyɔ lɛ hu abuu lɛ mli, shi enaaa ewɔŋ lɛ. Ni eje kpo yɛ Lea buu lɛ mli, ni ebote Rahel nɔ lɛ mli.
Shi Rahel ekɔlɔ amãgãi lɛ, ni ekɛwo yooma nɔ nii lɛ mli, ni eho eta nɔ. Laban nyɛmɔnyɛmɔɔ shi yɛ buu lɛ mli fɛɛ, shi enaaa.
Kɛkɛ ni Rahel kɛɛ etsɛ akɛ, “Ekafee minuŋtsɔ mlifu akɛ minyɛɛɛ shi mate yɛ ohiɛ ejaakɛ mifee yei anii.” No hewɔ lɛ, Laban tao amãgãi lɛ aahu, shi enaaa.
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob mli wo la, ni ekɛ Laban be. Yakob kɛɛ Laban akɛ, “Mɛɛ tɔ̃mɔ mitɔ̃, ni mɛɛ esha hu mifee, ni ohiɛ edɔ kɛnyiɛ misɛɛ nɛkɛ nɛɛ?
Kolɛ ni ota minibii lɛ fɛɛ mli nɛɛ, mɛni ona ni ji oshĩa nibii lɛ eko? Kɛji ona eko lɛ, okɛ sane nɛɛ aŋmɛ miwekumɛi kɛ bo hu owekumɛi nɛɛ ahiɛ koni amɛye wɔteŋ sane lɛ ni amɛbu bem ni amɛbu fɔ.
Mikɛ bo bahi shi nɛɛ, afii nyɔŋmai enyɔ sɔŋŋ nɛ; ogwantɛŋ yei kɛ obotia yei sharakeko, ni otoi lɛ ateŋ ojwɛnii lɛ hu miyeko eko.
Kooloi lɛ ateŋ nii ni kooloi awuiyelɔi tserɛɔ lɛ, mikɛbahãaa bo, mitoɔ bo najiaŋ. Nyɔɔŋ aju eko jio, shwane jio mi, midɛŋ oheɔ yɛ.
Bɔ ni mishihilɛ lɛ fee nɛ: latsaa tsaa mi shwane, ni fɛ̃i yeɔ mi nyɔɔŋ, ni wɔ hu tseɔ yɛ mihiɛ.

Afii nyɔŋmai enyɔ nɛɛ fɛɛ lɛ, bɔ ni miyɔɔ yɛ owe lɛ nɛ. Mikɛ emli afii nyɔŋma kɛ ejwɛ sɔ̃mɔ bo yɛ obiyei enyɔ lɛ ahewɔ ni mikɛ afii ekpaa hu sɔ̃mɔ bo kɛkwɛ otoi lɛ. Nɛkɛ be nɛɛ mli lɛ, otsake minyɔmɔwoo shii nyɔŋma sɔŋŋ.

Kɛjeee mitsɛ Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ, ni ji Abraham Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ mɔ ni Isak sheɔ lɛ lɛ ni kɛ mi yɔɔ jikulɛ, anɔkwale sane ji akɛ obaawo mi gbɛ kɛya kɛ midɛ folo. Shi Nyɔŋmɔ na mimanehulu kɛ mininenaa nitsumɔ ni naa wa lɛ, hewɔ ni ekã ohiɛ nyɔɔŋ nɛɛŋ lɛ.”
Laban here nɔ ni ekɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Biyei nɛɛ mibiyei ni, ni bii lɛ hu mibii ni; toi lɛ mitoi ni; ni nibii ni onaa nɛɛ fɛɛ lɛ minɔ ni. Shi ŋmɛnɛ mɛni manyɛ mafee mibiyei lɛ loo amɛbii ni amɛfɔfɔɔ lɛ?
No hewɔ lɛ, agbɛnɛ, ba ni mi kɛ bo akpãŋ koni no atsɔ̃ odase yɛ mi kɛ bo teŋ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob wo tɛ ema shi, ni ekɛto okadi;
ni ekɛɛ ewebii lɛ akɛ, “Nyɛbuaa tɛi anaa.” Amɛkɔlɔ tɛi, ni amɛto lɛ ku amɛma shi; ni amɛye nii yɛ jɛi yɛ tɛ ku lɛ he.
Laban wo tɛ ku lɛ Yegar-Sahaduta; shi Yakob lɛ, ewo lɛ Galed.
Laban kɛɛ akɛ, “Nɛkɛ tɛ ku nɛɛ miiye odase yɛ mi kɛ bo teŋ ŋmɛnɛ.” No hewɔ ni atsɛɔ tɛ lɛ akɛ Galed lɛ.
Atsɛɔ lɛ akɛ Mizpa hu ejaakɛ Laban kɛɛ akɛ, “Yehowa hiŋmɛi ahi mi kɛ bo fɛɛ he, be mli ni wɔgbala mli nɛɛ.
Kɛji owa mibiyei lɛ ayi aloo oooyaŋɔ yei krokomɛi ofata mibiyei lɛ ahe lɛ, gbɔmɔ ko bɛ biɛ moŋ, shi kaimɔ akɛ Nyɔŋmɔ ji odasefonyo yɛ mi kɛ bo teŋ.”
Laban saa ekɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Oona nɛkɛ tɛ ku ni ma shi nɛɛ, ni oona nɛkɛ okadi tɛ ni mikɛma mi kɛ bo teŋ nɛɛ.
Nɛkɛ tɛ ku nɛɛ ji odase, ni nɛkɛ okadi tɛ nɛɛ hu ji odase akɛ, mi lɛ, mihoŋ tɛ ku nɛɛ he mibaŋ oŋɔɔ ni mibafee bo efɔŋ, ni bo hu ohoŋ tɛ ku nɛɛ kɛ okadi tɛ nɛɛ he obaŋ miŋɔɔ ni obafee mi efɔŋ.
Abraham Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ kɛ Nahor Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ, amɛtsɛ Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ, afee kojolɔ yɛ wɔteŋ.” Kɛkɛ ni Yakob kã Mɔ ni gbeyei etsɛ Isak she lɛ kitã.
Kɛkɛ ni eshã afɔle yɛ gɔŋ lɛ nɔ, ni etsɛ ewekumɛi lɛ niyeli. Amɛye nii, ni amɛhi shi yɛ gɔŋ lɛ nɔ nyɔɔŋ lɛ mli fɛɛ.
Leebi maŋkpa lɛ, Laban te shi, ni eshwɔshwɔɔ enabii kɛ ebiyei lɛ anaa, ni ejɔɔ amɛ. Kɛkɛ ni Laban kɛ amɛ gbala mli, ni eku esɛɛ kɛtee emaŋ.
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob hu kɛshwie nɔ. Nyɔŋmɔ bɔfoi kɛ lɛ bakpe.
Be ni ena amɛ lɛ, ekɛɛ, “Enɛ lɛ Nyɔŋmɔ ta nɛ!” Ni ewo jɛi Mahanaim.
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob tsu mɛi kɛtsɔ ehiɛ kɛtee enyɛmi Esau ŋɔɔ yɛ Seir yɛ Edom shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ.
Wiemɔ ni ekɛtsu amɛ nɛ, “Nyɛkɛa minuŋtsɔ Esau akɛ, bɔ ni otsulɔ Yakob kɛɛ nɛ: ‘Miyato gbɔ yɛ Laban ŋɔɔ, ni mitsɛ yɛ jɛi aahu kɛbashi ŋmɛnɛ.
Minã tsinai kɛ tejii kɛ toi kɛ tsuji hii kɛ tsuji yei, ni mitsu ni abakɛɛ bo, minuŋtsɔ, koni kɛ miba lɛ ona mihe tsuijurɔ.’ ”
Mɛi ni atsu lɛ ku amɛsɛɛ amɛba Yakob ŋɔɔ, ni amɛbakɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Wɔtee onyɛmi Esau ŋɔɔ, ni lɛ hu ekɛ hii ohai ejwɛ miiba abakpee bo.”
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob tsui fã, ni efee yeyeeye naakpa. Eja emɛi lɛ kɛ toi lɛ kɛ tsinai lɛ kɛ yoomai lɛ amli kui enyɔ ni ekɛɛ,
“Kɛji Esau batua ku kome nɛɛ ni etswia amɛ nii lɛ, koni ku kome ni eshwɛ lɛ ana gbɛ ajo foi.”
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob sɔle ekɛɛ, “Mitsɛ Abraham Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ mitsɛ Isak Nyɔŋmɔ, Yehowa, bo mɔ ni okɛɛ mi akɛ, ‘Kuu osɛɛ oya oshikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ kɛ owekumɛi aŋɔɔ, ni mafee bo jogbaŋŋ’ lɛ,
osuɔmɔ ni tsakeee kɛ onɔkwayeli fɛɛ ni ojie kpo otsɔ̃ɔ otsulɔ lɛ, ekome folo nɛkɛ esaaa mi. Dɛhiɛmɔtso kɛkɛ mihiɛ kɛfo Yordan nɛɛ; shi agbɛnɛ mitsɔ asafo kui enyɔ.
Miikpa bo fai koni ojie mi yɛ Esau, minyɛmi lɛ, dɛŋ shi miishe lɛ gbeyei, koni ekaba ni ebatswia wɔ fɛɛ nii, mi kɛ nyɛmɛi lɛ kɛ bii lɛ.
Bo okɛɛ akɛ, ‘Mafee bo jogbaŋŋ, ni mahã oshwiei afa tamɔ ŋshɔnaa shia, ni anyɛŋ amɛyibɔ akane yɛ amɛyifalɛ naa.’ ”
No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob wɔ jɛi nakai gbi lɛ, ni ekɛ nii ni ehiɛ lɛ eko yake enyɛmi Esau;
too abotia yei ohai enyɔ kɛ too kpakpoi nyɔŋmai enyɔ, too gwantɛŋ yei ohai enyɔ kɛ too ojwɛnii nyɔŋmai enyɔ
kɛ yoomai nyɔŋmai etɛ̃ ni miihã amɛbii fufɔ lolo kɛ amɛbii lɛ, kɛ tsina hii nyɔŋma kɛ tsina yei nyɔŋmai ejwɛ kɛ teji yei nyɔŋmai enyɔ kɛ teji hii nyɔŋma.
Yakob kɛ nibii nɛɛ wo etsuji lɛ adɛŋ kuikui, ni ekɛɛ tsuji lɛ akɛ, “Nyɛtsɔa mihiɛ ni nyɛhãa gbɛ akãa ku kɛ ku teŋ.”
Yakob wo klɛŋklɛŋ ku lɛ nɔkwɛlɔ lɛ kitã akɛ, “Kɛji minyɛmi Esau kɛ bo kpe ni ebi bo akɛ, ‘Namɔ gbɔmɔ ji bo, ni nɛgbɛ oyaa, ni namɔ nii ji enɛɛmɛi ni nyiɛ ohiɛ nɛɛ?’ lɛ,
no lɛ ohã lɛ hetoo akɛ, ‘Otsulɔ Yakob nikeenii ni ekɛtsu akɛ akɛbake minuŋtsɔ Esau ni; ni naa, lɛ diɛŋtsɛ lɛ enyiɛ wɔsɛɛ?’ ”
Nakai kitã nɔŋŋ ewo mɔ ni ji enyɔ kɛ mɔ ni ji etɛ̃ lɛ kɛ mɛi fɛɛ hu ni nyiɛ kui lɛ asɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Kɛ nyɛnina Esau lɛ, bɔ ni nyɛkɛ lɛ awie nɛ;
ni nyɛsaa nyɛkɛa lɛ akɛ, naa ‘Otsulɔ Yakob nyiɛ wɔsɛɛ.’ ” Esusumɔ ji akɛ, “Mikɛ nikeenii ni nyiɛ hiɛ nɛɛ yaakpãtã lɛ, ni no sɛɛ dani mayana ehiɛ; eko lɛ eeekwɛ mihiɛ.”
Kɛkɛ ni akɛ nikeenii lɛ tsɔ Yakob hiɛ, shi lɛ diɛŋtsɛ lɛ, ekɛ mɛi ni eshwɛ lɛ wɔ jɛi nakai gbi lɛ.
Yakob te shi nyɔɔŋ lɛ mli, ni ekɛ eŋãmɛi enyɔ lɛ kɛ eweyei enyɔ lɛ kɛ ebihii nyɔŋma kɛ ekome lɛ yafo faa lɛ yɛ Yabok faafoohe lɛ.
Ehã amɛfo faa lɛ kɛ nii ni eyɔɔ fɛɛ.
Ni ebashwɛ Yakob kome. Nuu ko kɛ lɛ banɔ kɛyashi jetsɛremɔ.
Be ni nuu lɛ na akɛ enyɛɛɛ Yakob lɛ, etswa Yakob joŋku nɔ, ni joŋku talɔ lɛ hwãŋ yɛ nɔmɔ lɛ mli.
Nuu lɛ kɛɛ akɛ, “Hã maya, shi je miitsɛre!” Shi Yakob kɛɛ akɛ, “Mihaŋ oya, ja ojɔɔ mi dã.”
Nuu lɛ bi Yakob akɛ, “Te atsɛɔ bo tɛŋŋ?” Yakob to he akɛ, “Atsɛɔ mi Yakob.”
Nuu lɛ kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Atsɛŋ bo Yakob dɔŋŋ, shi Israel aaatsɛ bo, ejaakɛ okɛ Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ gbɔmɛi eshi mple, ni oye kunim.”
Yakob kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Miikpa bo fai ni otsɔ̃ɔ mi ogbɛi.” Shi nuu lɛ kɛɛ, “Mɛni hewɔ obiɔ migbɛi?” Ni ejɔɔ Yakob moŋ yɛ jɛi.
Yakob kɛɛ akɛ, “Mina Nyɔŋmɔ hiɛ kɛ hiɛ, shi kɛ̃lɛ migbooo.” No hewɔ lɛ, ewo jɛi Peniel.
Be ni efoŋ yɛ Peniel lɛ, je etsɛre lɛ, ni eetsutsɔ egboŋ.
No hewɔ lɛ, kɛbashi ŋmɛnɛ Israelbii yeee joŋku he loo, ejaakɛ nuu lɛ tswa Yakob joŋku lɛ nɔ, ni ejoŋku lɛ hwãŋ.
Yakob wo ehiɛ nɔ ekwɛ, ni naa Esau miiba kɛ mɛi ohai ejwɛ. No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob ja gbekɛbii lɛ amli ehã Lea kɛ Rahel kɛ weyei enyɔ lɛ.
Ekɛ weyei lɛ kɛ amɛbii lɛ to hiɛgbɛ; Lea kɛ ebii lɛ nyiɛ amɛsɛɛ; ni Rahel kɛ Yosef nyiɛ sɛɛ kwraa.
Shi lɛ Yakob lɛ diɛŋtsɛ lɛ eho eyi ekui lɛ fɛɛ ahiɛ; ni be ni eyaa lɛ ekoto shi flɛoflɛo shii kpawo dani eyashɛ enyɛmi lɛ ŋɔɔ.
Shi Esau sha foi ekɛ lɛ bakpe. Eloo Yakob atuu, ni eho egbee ekuɛ nɔ, ni eshwɔ enaa, ni amɛfo.
Be ni Esau wo ehiɛ nɔ ni ena yei lɛ kɛ gbekɛbii lɛ, ebi Yakob akɛ, “Namɛi ji mɛi ni kɛ bo nyiɛ nɛɛ?” Ni Yakob to he akɛ, “Bii ni Nyɔŋmɔ eduro otsulɔ lɛ ni.”
Kɛkɛ ni weyei lɛ tsi ba, amɛ kɛ amɛbii lɛ, ni amɛbakoto Esau.
Lea hu kɛ ebii lɛ tsi ba ni amɛbakoto Esau. Ni naagbee kwraa lɛ Yosef kɛ Rahel hu ba ni amɛbakoto lɛ.
Kɛkɛ ni Esau bi akɛ, “Kuikui ni mikɛkpe nɛɛ fɛɛ lɛ te eshishi hu?”
Shi Esau kɛɛ akɛ, “Minyɛmi nuu, nɔ ni miyɔɔ lɛ fa, hã onɔ lɛ ahi shi ahã bo!”
Shi Yakob kɛɛ, “Dabida; miikpa bo fai, kɛji mina hiɛ yɛ ohiɛ lɛ, no lɛ hemɔ midɛŋ nikeenii lɛ; ejaakɛ ohiɛ ni mina nɛɛ lɛ etamɔ nɔ ni mina Nyɔŋmɔ hiɛ pɛ, ni ohere mi atuu hu.
Miikpa bo fai koni ohe midɛŋ nikeenii ni akɛbahã bo nɛɛ; ejaakɛ Nyɔŋmɔ eduro mi, ni misaa miyɛ nɔ fɛɛ nɔ hu.” Ni Yakob hiɛ Esau kɛ wiemɔ aahu kɛyashi be ni ehe nikeenii lɛ.
Esau kɛɛ, “Hã ni wɔŋɔ shwie nɔ koni wɔya; mi lɛ matsɔ ohiɛ.”
Shi Yakob kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Minuŋtsɔ le akɛ gbekɛbii lɛ ahiɛ esako; asaŋ mihiɛ toi kɛ tsinai ni hãa amɛbii fufɔ; amɛsane kã mitsui nɔ; kɛji atsirɛ amɛyisɛɛ gbi kome jenamɔ lɛ, kooloi lɛ fɛɛ aaabagboi.
No hewɔ lɛ, minuŋtsɔ atsɔ̃ etsulɔ hiɛ, ni mi lɛ manyiɛ blɛooblɛoo bɔ ni kooloi lɛ ni nyiɛ mihiɛ lɛ kɛ gbekɛbii lɛ aaanyɛ anyiɛ kɛyaashi beyinɔ ni mashɛ minuŋtsɔ ŋɔɔ yɛ Edom.”
Ni Esau kɛɛ, “Hã mashi mɛi ni kɛ mi nyiɛ lɛ eko mato ohe.” Yakob to he akɛ, “Mɛɛ hiamɔ ehia? Hã mi mana hiɛ yɛ minuŋtsɔ hiɛ kɛkɛ!”
Kɛkɛ ni Esau ku esɛɛ nakai gbi lɛ, ni eyiŋ kɛtee Edom.
Yakob kɛshwie nɔ kɛtee Sukot ni eyama etsu yɛ jɛi, ni efee asesei ehã ekooloi lɛ. No hewɔ lɛ, awo jɛi Sukot.
Be ni Yakob ku esɛɛ kɛjɛ Mesopotamia ebaa lɛ, ebashɛ Kanaan shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ maŋ ko ni ji Shekem lɛ shweshweeshwe, ni eto shi yɛ maŋ lɛ klotia.
Yakob kane shika jwiɛtɛi kukuji oha, ni ekɛhe shikpɔŋ he ni ebato shi yɛ lɛ yɛ Hamorbii lɛ adɛŋ. Shekem tsɛ ji Hamor nɛɛ.
Yakob ma afɔleshãa latɛ yɛ jɛi, ni ewo lɛ gbɛi akɛ “El, Israel Nyɔŋmɔ lɛ.”
Gbi ko lɛ Dina, Lea biyoo ni ekɛ Yakob fɔ lɛ, je kpo etee Kanaan shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ yei komɛi saramɔ.
Shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ lumɔ ni atsɛɔ lɛ Shekem, Harmor Hivnyo lɛ, binuu na Dina, ni emɔ lɛ ekɛ lɛ wɔ akrananaa, ni efite lɛ.
Shekem tsui mɔ Yakob biyoo Dina lɛ, ni esumɔ oblayoo lɛ, ni ekɛ lɛ wie tsuijurɔ naa.
Shekem kɛɛ etsɛ Hamor akɛ, “Yaakpee oblayoo nɛɛ ohã mi.”
Agbɛnɛ Yakob nu akɛ abule ebiyoo Dina. Shi no mli lɛ, ebihii lɛ kɛ ekooloi lɛ yɛ ŋa lɛ nɔ. Hewɔ lɛ Yakob mɔ enaabu mli kɛyashi be ni amɛba.
Shekem tsɛ Hamor tee Yakob ŋɔɔ, koni ekɛ lɛ ayawie Dina he.
Be ni Yakob bihii lɛ nu he lɛ, amɛjɛ ŋa lɛ nɔ amɛba. Edɔ oblahii nɛɛ, ni amɛmli wo la naakpa ejaakɛ afee hiɛgbejianii yɛ Israel, akɛni nuu lɛ kɛ Yakob biyoo lɛ wɔ, shi esaaa akɛ afeɔ nakai nɔ ko lɛ.
Shi Hamor kɛ amɛ wie ekɛɛ, “Mibinuu Shekem tsui emɔ nyɛbiyoo lɛ; miikpa nyɛ fai koni nyɛkɛ lɛ ahã lɛ gbãlã.
Nyɛkɛ wɔ ayea yooŋɔɔ; nyɛkɛ nyɛbiyei lɛ ahãa wɔ gbãlã, ni nyɛ hu nyɛŋɔa wɔbiyei nyɛfea ŋamɛi.
Nyɛkɛ wɔ ahia shi. Shikpɔŋ lɛ kã shi hã nyɛ; nyɛhia nɔ ni nyɛtsua nɔ nii koni nyɛna nii yɛ nɔ nyɛhãa nyɛhe akɛ nyɛnɔ.”
Kɛkɛ ni Shekem kɛɛ Dina tsɛ kɛ enyɛmimɛi lɛ akɛ, “Nyɛhãa mihiɛ abaa nyam yɛ nyɛhiɛ shi nɔ fɛɛ nɔ ni nyɛaabi mi lɛ mahã nyɛ.
Nyɛbia mi gbãlãnii kɛ nikeenii; bɔ fɛɛ bɔ ni nyɛtaoɔ lɛ, mahã nyɛ koni nyɛkɛ oblayoo lɛ ahã mi.”
Yakob bii lɛ laka Shekem kɛ etsɛ Hamor hiɛ ejaakɛ Shekem ebule amɛnyɛmi yoo Dina lɛ.
Yakob bii lɛ kɛɛ Shekem kɛ etsɛ Hamor akɛ, “Wɔnyɛŋ nɛkɛ nɔ ko wɔfee ni wɔkɛ wɔnyɛmi yoo ahã mɔ ko ni ji foolɔ ejaakɛ no lɛ wɔto kpa.
Nɔ ni wɔtaoɔ kɛkɛ dani wɔɔkpɛ̃lɛ nɔ wɔhã nyɛ ji akɛ nyɛbaatsɔmɔ tamɔ wɔ, ni abaafolɔ nyɛteŋ hii lɛ fɛɛ ketia.
No lɛ wɔkɛ wɔbiyei baahã nyɛ gbãlã, ni wɔ hu wɔɔŋɔ nyɛbiyei, ni wɔkɛ nyɛ aaahi shi, ni wɔɔtsɔ̃ maŋ kome.
Shi kɛji nyɛbooo wɔ toi koni nyɛhã afo nyɛ ketia lɛ, no lɛ wɔɔŋɔ wɔbiyoo lɛ ni wɔya.”
Wiemɔ nɛɛ sa Hamor kɛ ebi Shekem hiɛ.
Oblanyo lɛ kɛ sane lɛ shashaooo shi, ejaakɛ etsui emɔ Yakob biyoo lɛ. Oblanyo nɛɛ abuɔ lɛ fe etsɛ we lɛ mli bii fɛɛ.
No hewɔ lɛ, Hamor kɛ ebi Shekem tee agbonaa koi lɛ shi, ni amɛkɛ amɛmaŋ lɛ mli hii lɛ wie amɛkɛɛ,
“Gbɔmɛi nɛɛ kɛ wɔ ye yɛ hejɔlɛ mli; no hewɔ lɛ, nyɛhãa amɛhia shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ, ni amɛtsu nɔ nii. Shikpɔŋ lɛ hu da aahu hã amɛ. Nyɛhãa wɔŋɔa amɛbiyei lɛ, ni wɔ hu wɔkɛ wɔbiyei lɛ ahã amɛ gbãlã.
Shi ja afo wɔteŋ hii fɛɛ ketia tamɔ bɔ ni afo amɛ lɛ dani gbɔmɛi lɛ aaakpɛ̃lɛ ni amɛkɛ wɔ ahi shi ni amɛkɛ wɔ aaafee maŋ kome.
Amɛkooloo kui kɛ amɛnii ni amɛyɔɔ kɛ amɛshĩa kooloi fɛɛ lɛ, ani jeee wɔnii ebaatsɔmɔ? Nyɛhãa wɔkpɛ̃lɛa nɔ wɔhãa amɛ kɛkɛ koni amɛkɛ wɔ ahi shi.”
Kɛkɛ ni maŋbii lɛ fɛɛ ni tee agbonaa koi lɛ shi lɛ ŋɔ nɔ ni Hamor kɛ ebi Shekem kɛɛ lɛ nɔ, ni afolɔ Shekem maŋ lɛ mli hii fɛɛ ni eshɛ tayaa lɛ ketia.
Shi gbi ni ji etɛ̃ lɛ nɔ, be ni amɛfaji lɛ ewo wu lɛ, Yakob bihii enyɔ ni ji Simeon kɛ Levi, Dina nyɛmimɛi lɛ, kɔlɔ amɛklantei, ni amɛbatua maŋ lɛ trukaa, ni amɛgbe hii lɛ fɛɛ.
Amɛkɛ klante gbe Hamor kɛ ebi Shekem hu, ni amɛyaŋɔ Dina yɛ Shekem we lɛ, ni amɛyiŋ amɛtee.
Yakob bii krokomɛi lɛ banina mɛi ni enyɔnyɔɔ lɛ, ni amɛha maŋ lɛ mli nii, ejaakɛ Shekem ebule amɛnyɛmi yoo lɛ.
Shekem maŋbii lɛ atoi kɛ amɛtsinai kɛ amɛtejii kɛ amɛnii ni yɔɔ maŋ lɛ mli kɛ nii ni yɔɔ ŋa nɔ lɛ, Yakob bii lɛ loo fɛɛ kɛtee.
Amɛsaa amɛŋɔ maŋbii lɛ ajwetri fɛɛ kɛ amɛbii bibii fɛɛ kɛ amɛŋamɛi fɛɛ nom, ni amɛha amɛwei amli nibii fɛɛ.

Kɛkɛ ni Yakob kɛɛ Simeon kɛ Levi akɛ, “Nyɛwo mi amaneŋ, ni nyɛhã shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ bii ni ji Kanaanbii kɛ Perizbii lɛ baanyaŋe mi. Ni mi hu nɛ, ni miyikulɛ ji fioo nɛɛ. Kɛji amɛaabua amɛhe naa amɛbatua mi lɛ, amɛaagbe mi, ni amɛaakpãtã miwe lɛ hiɛ.” 31Shi Simeon kɛ Levi kɛɛ, “Ani eja gbɛ akɛ afee wɔnyɛmi yoo lɛ tamɔ afeɔ ajwamãŋ ko kɛkɛ lo?”
Nyɔŋmɔ kɛɛ Yakob akɛ, “Yaa Betel ni oyahi jɛi, ni oma afɔleshãa latɛ yɛ jɛi ohã Nyɔŋmɔ ni jie ehe kpo etsɔ̃ɔ bo be ni ojo onyɛmi Esau naa foi lɛ.”
No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob kɛɛ ewe lɛ kɛ mɛi fɛɛ ni kɛ lɛ yɔɔ lɛ akɛ, “Nyɛjiea maŋsɛɛ wɔji ni yɔɔ nyɛteŋ lɛ nyɛshɛraa nyɛshwiea, ni nyɛtsua nyɛhe ni nyɛtsakea nyɛtadei.
Nyɛhãa wɔyaa Betel koni mayama afɔleshãa latɛ yɛ jɛi mahã Nyɔŋmɔ, mɔ ni bo misɔlemɔ toi yɛ mifimɔ gbi lɛ nɔ ni ewa mi yɛ gbɛ ni mifã lɛ fɛɛ mli lɛ.”
No hewɔ lɛ, amɛkɛ maŋsɛɛ wɔji lɛ fɛɛ ni yɔɔ amɛdɛŋ lɛ kɛ amɛtoiaŋnii lɛ bahã Yakob; kɛkɛ ni Yakob kɛtee eyafu yɛ tso kpele ko ni ma Shekem masɛi lɛ shishi.
Kɛkɛ ni amɛŋɔ shwie nɔ. Nyɔŋmɔ he ŋmiŋmi mɔmɔ maji fɛɛ ni bɔle amɛ lɛ, no hewɔ lɛ, amɛtiuuu Yakob webii lɛ. 6Yakob kɛ mɛi fɛɛ ni ekɛnyiɛ lɛ bashɛ Luz ni ji Betel ni yɔɔ Kanaan shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ lɛ.
Ema afɔleshãa latɛ yɛ jɛi, ni etsɛ jɛi El-Betel, ejaakɛ jɛi Nyɔŋmɔ jie ehe shi etsɔ̃ɔ lɛ yɛ, be ni ejo enyɛmi Esau naa foi lɛ.
Ni Debora, mɔ ni kwɛɔ Rebeka kɛjɛ egbekɛbiiashi lɛ, gbo ni afu lɛ yɛ Betel wuoyigbɛ yɛ tso kpele ko shishi. No hewɔ lɛ, awo tso lɛ gbɛi akɛ Allon-bakut.
Ni Nyɔŋmɔ jie ehe kpo etsɔ̃ɔ Yakob ekoŋŋ, be ni ejɛ Mesopotamia eba lɛ, ni ejɔɔ lɛ.
Nyɔŋmɔ kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Ogbɛi ji Yakob; atsɛŋ bo Yakob dɔŋŋ, shi moŋ aaatsɛ bo Israel.” No hewɔ lɛ, Nyɔŋmɔ wo lɛ Israel.
Nyɔŋmɔ kɛɛ lɛ akɛ, “Mi ji Nyɔŋmɔ Ofe lɛ; fɔ ni oyi afa. Maŋ kɛ maji babaoo aaajɛ omli, ni maŋtsɛmɛi hu aaajɛ omli.
Shikpɔŋ lɛ ni mikɛhã Abraham kɛ Isak lɛ, bo mikɛbaahã, ni oshwiei ni aaaba yɛ osɛɛ lɛ mikɛ shikpɔŋ nɛɛ baahã.”
Kɛkɛ ni Nyɔŋmɔ shi Yakob yɛ he ni ekɛ lɛ wie yɛ lɛ, ni etee ŋwɛi.
Yakob ŋɔ tɛ eto okadi yɛ he ni Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ lɛ wie yɛ lɛ, ni efɔse wain kɛ mu eshwie nɔ.
No hewɔ lɛ, Yakob wo he ni Nyɔŋmɔ kɛ lɛ wie yɛ lɛ gbɛi akɛ Betel.
Kɛkɛ ni Yakob kɛ ewebii lɛ fã kɛjɛ Betel. Be ni eshwɛ gbɛ kukuoo ko lolo dani amɛshɛɔ Efrat lɛ, Rahel bɔi kɔ̃ɔmɔ, ni kɔ̃ɔmɔ lɛ mli yawa.
Be ni fɔmɔ lɛ mli ewa nɛkɛ lɛ, yoofɔlɔ lɛ kɛɛ Rahel akɛ, “Kaashe gbeyei, ejaakɛ obaafɔ nuu ekoŋŋ.”
Be ni Rahel etɔ biti ni eehe enyɔ lɛ, ewo abifao lɛ gbɛi akɛ Benoni; shi etsɛ wo lɛ Benyamin.
Rahel gbo ni afu lɛ yɛ Efrat ni ji Betlehem gbɛ lɛ he.
Yakob kɛ tɛ ko to okadi yɛ Rahel saŋ lɛ nɔ; ni no hewɔ lɛ, atsɛɔ lɛ Rahel saŋ nɔ tɛ kɛbashi ŋmɛnɛ.
Israel ni atsɛɔ lɛ Yakob hu lɛ tsa egbɛfaa lɛ nɔ, ni eyashi ebuu lɛ yɛ Eder mɔɔ lɛ sɛɛgbɛ.
Be ni Yakob yɔɔ nakai shikpɔŋ lɛ nɔ lɛ, Ruben yi mli etee ekɛ etsɛ hemɔ Bilha lɛ yawɔ; Yakob nu sane nɛɛ he. Yakob yɛ bihii nyɔŋma kɛ enyɔ.
Lea bihii ji Ruben, Yakob kromɔbi lɛ, kɛ Simeon kɛ Levi kɛ Yuda kɛ Isakar kɛ Zebulon.
Rahel bihii ji Yosef kɛ Benyamin.
Bilha, Rahel weyoo lɛ, bihii ji Dan kɛ Naftali.
Ni Zilpa, Lea weyoo lɛ, bii ji Gad kɛ Asher. Mɛnɛɛmɛi ji Yakob bihii lɛ ni efɔ yɛ Mesopotamia lɛ.
Yakob ba etsɛ Isak ŋɔɔ yɛ Mamre loo Kiriat-Arba ni bɛŋkɛ Hebron lɛ, he ni Abraham kɛ Isak bato gbɔ yɛ lɛ.
Afii ni Isak ye ji afii oha kɛ nyɔŋmai kpaanyɔ.
Isak tsɔ̃ nuumo ni egbɔ kotokoto; egbo ni afu lɛ yɛ ewekumɛi amasɛi be mli ni eye afii babaoo lɛ. Ni ebii ni ji Esau kɛ Yakob fu lɛ.
